  <!-- FAQ -->
  <h2 id="faq" class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy mb-4 mt-10">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
  <div class="space-y-3 mb-8 not-prose">
    <details class="bg-white rounded-xl border-l-4 border-gold/40 p-5 shadow-sm">
      <summary class="font-semibold text-navy cursor-pointer">What options are commonly added to a disc stack centrifuge system?</summary>
      <p class="text-text-light mt-3 text-sm">Common options include: feed pump (gear, peristaltic, or progressive cavity), pre-heater (electric or steam shell-and-tube), duplex basket strainer (pre-filtration), sludge tank with agitator, clean fluid tank, chemical injection (demulsifier or anti-foaming), VFD for bowl speed control, PLC with HMI for automated control, and CIP circuit for sanitary applications.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="bg-white rounded-xl border-l-4 border-gold/40 p-5 shadow-sm">
      <summary class="font-semibold text-navy cursor-pointer">Do I need a pre-heater for my disc stack centrifuge?</summary>
      <p class="text-text-light mt-3 text-sm">A pre-heater is required for any application where the process fluid has viscosity above 50 cSt, or where the feed contains wax or asphaltene components that solidify below 120°F. Heavy fuel oil (HFO), crude oil, and waste oil applications almost always require pre-heating to 180–200°F. Coolant and water-based fluid applications typically do not require heating.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="bg-white rounded-xl border-l-4 border-gold/40 p-5 shadow-sm">
      <summary class="font-semibold text-navy cursor-pointer">What is a duplex basket strainer and do I need one?</summary>
      <p class="text-text-light mt-3 text-sm">A duplex basket strainer is a two-body in-line filter with switching valves that allows continuous operation while one basket is cleaned. It protects the centrifuge from large solid particles (50–500 micron) that would accelerate bowl wear or clog the feed inlet. Recommended for crude oil, waste oil, and machining coolant applications with intermittent large particles.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="bg-white rounded-xl border-l-4 border-gold/40 p-5 shadow-sm">
      <summary class="font-semibold text-navy cursor-pointer">Should my disc centrifuge system have a PLC controller?</summary>
      <p class="text-text-light mt-3 text-sm">A PLC with HMI is strongly recommended for any production centrifuge. It automates startup/shutdown, controls sludge ejection cycle timing, monitors operating water and flow, handles alarm conditions, and logs data. PLC control eliminates the need for constant operator attention and reduces costly mistakes during manual operation. Dolphin Centrifuge designs and builds complete control panels for all DMPX systems.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="bg-white rounded-xl border-l-4 border-gold/40 p-5 shadow-sm">
      <summary class="font-semibold text-navy cursor-pointer">Can Dolphin Centrifuge build a complete turnkey centrifuge system with all accessories?</summary>
      <p class="text-text-light mt-3 text-sm">Yes. Dolphin Centrifuge designs, fabricates, and factory-tests complete turnkey disc stack centrifuge systems with all selected options integrated on a single skid. Systems are fully assembled, electrically integrated, and hydraulic/pressure tested at our Warren, MI facility before shipment. All DMPX and DMB series systems are available as turnkey packages with any combination of the options described on this page.</p>
    </details>
  </div>
